+Title ideas:
+
+Local-First Software strengthens Democracy
+
+A local-first stack to build software that strengthens democracy
+
+Local-First Software to Shorten the Coming Darkness
+
+Digital Ecosystems to Strenghten Democracy
+
+A blueprint for shortening the coming digital darkness
+
+Intro:
+
+People are drowning in slop, ethics and competence are becoming liabilities, and each day the light of humanity seems to dim a bit more
+
+But a growing number of people are fighting back
+
+I can only speak on the systems I know something about, which are the engineered systems that keep society together, so I fill restrict the focus of this talk to them, but there are ofc others (e.g. agriculture) that I'm sure we'll hear more about today from others too
+
+A lot of what I will be talking about today is essentially copied from the Modal Collective page
+
+Stacks and ideas:
+
+Linux
+systemd
+GNOME
+Flatpak
+p2panda
+
+modal.cx Goals
+
+- A secure Free Desktop
+- Phones without Monopolies
+- Local-First Collaboration
+- Image-Based OSes
+- Hardware Longevity
+- Ecosystem of Respectful Apps
+
+modal.cx Principles
+
+- Software Freedom
+- Built For Everyone
+- Design-First
+- Vertical Integration
+- Collapse Awareness
+- Adversarial Security Posture
+- Post-Internet
+- Post-Web
+- Upstream-First
+- Respect for Attention
+
+RISC-V and the ecosystem around it (the silicon version of this)
+
+Other vaguely related things (fediverse, 3D printing & makerspaces etc.)
+
+p2panda and general local-first stack section:
+
+Transports/Networks (IP, Bluetooth, NAN, Mesh, sneakernet (USB sticks etc.))
+CRDTs
+Protocols and state machines (p2panda, weron/panrpc, BitTorrent, IPFS, ActivityPub etc.)
+Moderation and media (ActivityPub)
+p2panda internals
+
+Analog Twin and pen and paper office + courier fallbacks as a way to protect us against digital system collapse
+
+Example: Reflection (demo on Laptop, Tablet and Phone)
+
+Import the talk from VanLUG for the GTK stack and merge them into a Codeberg repo (or maybe just create a new Codeberg repo?)
+
+Example: Inkling: p2panda-powered app to share ideas with others in a talk (live coding) (demo on Laptop, Tablet and Phone)

